                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13114117" author="jeromatron" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2011 02:06:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this the same as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3236&quot; title=&quot;nodetool scrub hangs at 100% complete&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3236&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3236&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114118" author="alienth" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2011 02:16:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep, didn&apos;t see that. I&apos;m fine with closing this as a duplicate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114144" author="alienth" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2011 04:54:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, the other issue claims that the scrub is hanging. The issue I&apos;ve listed here is that the information just persists even after completion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is very easy to test. Just create a CF, add some data, flush, and then run scrub a few times in a row. The scrubs will all complete, but all of the info from the scrubs will stick around in &apos;compactionstats&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13116539" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2011 15:26:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on Pavel&apos;s patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13116563" author="xedin" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2011 15:52:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
